Chapter 5: Train Youth as Stewards
Core Question
How do young people become guardians of the blueprint?
Understand
Youth should not inherit only problems.
They should inherit tools.
They should learn:
How to read a ledger
 How to take meeting notes
 How to ask good questions
 How to interview elders
 How to protect privacy
 How to understand property records
 How to support businesses
 How to organize preparedness
 How to testify publicly
 How to build a report
 How to facilitate a meeting
 How to use technology responsibly
 How to challenge extraction
 How to remember history
 How to carry covenant
Youth stewardship means young people are not spectators.
They are apprentices in responsibility.
Give youth real roles with protection, mentorship, and review.
Do not use youth as decoration.
Train them into governance.
Discuss
Which young people are ready for responsibility?
What skills should they learn first?
Who can mentor them consistently?
What role can they practice safely?
What output should they create?
How will elders and youth learn from each other?
Build: Youth Stewardship Track
