PART THREE: TRANSFER RESPONSIBILITY

Chapter 7: Create a Succession Plan
Core Question
Who carries the work if current leaders step back?
Understand
Succession is not an emergency plan after someone leaves.
Succession is a standing practice.
A society should know who can step into each key role.
Key roles may include:
Founder/Admin
 Facilitator
 Treasurer
 Assistant Treasurer
 Recordkeeper
 Care Coordinator
 Business Liaison
 Property Liaison
 Youth Liaison
 Preparedness Lead
 Elder Liaison
 Civic Lead
 Federation Representative
 Archive Keeper
 Training Coordinator
Succession does not mean pushing leaders out.
It means making sure the work does not collapse if they rest, move, become ill, change capacity, or complete their season.
Succession is respect for the leader and protection for the society.
Discuss
Which roles depend too much on one person?
Who could step in temporarily?
Who needs training?
What access would need to transfer?
What procedures must be written?
What role should have a deputy immediately?
