Chapter 8: Create Role Manuals
Core Question
Can someone else learn the role without guessing?
Understand
A role manual turns personal knowledge into institutional knowledge.
Each key role should have a simple manual.
A role manual should explain:
Purpose of the role
 Responsibilities
 Weekly/monthly tasks
 What records are handled
 What meetings are attended
 What decisions the role can make
 What decisions require approval
 What privacy rules apply
 What tools are used
 What reports are produced
 Who the backup is
 What to do during transition
A manual does not need to be long.
It needs to be useful.
If a role has no manual, the society is depending on memory.
Discuss
Which role needs a manual first?
What does that person do that others do not see?
What decisions can the role make?
What records does the role handle?
What privacy rules apply?
What would a new person need to know first?
Build: Role Manual Template
