Chapter 10: Transfer Access Safely
Core Question
How do we pass responsibility without risking money, records, or privacy?
Understand
Succession includes access transfer.
Access may include:
Bank/payment tools
 Ledger
 Simba admin rights
 Document archive
 Meeting records
 Member information
 Care team notes
 Youth records
 Elder records
 Property records
 Business campaign tools
 Preparedness contact lists
 Email lists
 Social media
 Website
 Shared drives
 Public communication channels
 Legal documents
 Insurance documents
Access should never be transferred casually.
The society needs a process.
Who approves access?
What access is role-specific?
What access is temporary?
What access must be removed when someone leaves a role?
What access requires two-person oversight?
What access should be audited?
Safe access protects trust.
Discuss
Who currently has access to what?
Who has access they no longer need?
What access does each role require?
What access is too sensitive for one person?
How will access be reviewed?
What happens when someone leaves?
