PART FIVE: REPORT LEGACY

Chapter 15: Legacy Dashboard
Core Question
Are we preserving and transferring the blueprint?
Understand
A legacy dashboard measures continuity.
Not popularity.
Not likes.
Not event attendance only.
It should track:
Archive completeness
 Founding story recorded
 Elder interviews completed
 Youth stewards trained
 Role manuals created
 Succession roles filled
 Leadership rotations completed
 Access reviews completed
 Annual covenant renewal
 Generational covenant created
 Builder-to-builder transfers
 Reports archived
 Media consent records
 Public story protections
 Training sessions completed
 Procedures documented
 Next generation leaders active
The dashboard should help the society see whether the work can continue.
