Chapter 16: Legacy and Succession Report
Core Question
What can now be inherited?
Understand
The Legacy and Succession Report should answer:
What memory was preserved?
 What records were organized?
 What stories were protected?
 What youth were trained?
 What elders were honored?
 What roles have successors?
 What access was transferred safely?
 What leadership rotations happened?
 What curriculum was created?
 What covenant was renewed?
 What procedures were documented?
 What remains fragile?
 What must be passed forward next?
This report is not a farewell.
It is a transfer document.
It tells the next generation:
Here is what we built.
Here is what we learned.
Here is what we protected.
Here is what still needs your hands.
