 [ ] Generational Covenant
 [ ] Builder-to-Builder Transfer Plan
 [ ] Story Protection Policy
 [ ] Legacy Dashboard
 [ ] Legacy and Succession Report
Final question:
Can the blueprint survive us?

Closing Principle
The work is not complete because one generation built something.
The work becomes complete when the next generation can understand it, question it, repair it, adapt it, and carry it forward.
Legacy is not control from the past.
Legacy is responsibility passed with enough structure to survive change.
Do not leave only stories.
Leave records.
Do not leave only inspiration.
Leave procedures.
Do not leave only founders.
Leave trained successors.
Do not leave only property.
Leave stewardship.
Do not leave only money.
Leave habits.
Do not leave only history.
Leave a living blueprint.
Systems are love that learned to last.
The work is not complete until it can be inherited.

